begin
reserve I for set;
reserve x for set;
reserve C for Category;
theorem
Th22: (for F,G being (Function of I,(the carrier' of C)) holds (( doms F ) = ( cods G ) implies (( doms ( F "*" G ) ) = ( doms G ) & ( cods ( F "*" G ) ) = ( cods F ))))
proof
let F being (Function of I,(the carrier' of C)),G being (Function of I,(the carrier' of C));
assume that
A1: ( doms F ) = ( cods G );
now
let x;
assume A2: x in I;
then A3: ( cod ( G /. x ) ) = ( ( doms F ) /. x ) by A1,CKB8:def 1
.= ( dom ( F /. x ) ) by A2,CKB7:def 1;
thus ( ( doms ( F "*" G ) ) /. x ) = ( dom ( ( F "*" G ) /. x ) ) by A2,CKB7:def 1
.= ( dom ( ( F /. x ) * ( G /. x ) ) ) by A2,CKB27:def 1
.= ( dom ( G /. x ) ) by A3,CAT_1:17
.= ( ( doms G ) /. x ) by A2,CKB7:def 1;
end;
hence ( doms ( F "*" G ) ) = ( doms G ) by CKB2:1;
now
let x;
assume A4: x in I;
then A5: ( cod ( G /. x ) ) = ( ( doms F ) /. x ) by A1,CKB8:def 1
.= ( dom ( F /. x ) ) by A4,CKB7:def 1;
thus ( ( cods ( F "*" G ) ) /. x ) = ( cod ( ( F "*" G ) /. x ) ) by A4,CKB8:def 1
.= ( cod ( ( F /. x ) * ( G /. x ) ) ) by A4,CKB27:def 1
.= ( cod ( F /. x ) ) by A5,CAT_1:17
.= ( ( cods F ) /. x ) by A4,CKB8:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by CKB2:1;
end;
